main event: A metallic object was observed at the rear of a paint and hardware store in Melbourne, Florida on August 17, 1960.
interesting points: The object was approximately 2 to 3 feet long and 18 inches wide.
The object appeared to be made of metal and was shaped in an irregular fashion.
The object was located near the rear of the building, partially obscured from view.
There were no markings or obvious identification on the object.
Witnesses reported that the object appeared to have been there for some time, though they were unsure of its origins or purpose.
photographs: yes, the report includes two photographs
